    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> With reference to the note which I had the
                            honor to address to you on the 23d of December last, and to the answer
                            which you were so good as to make to it, on the 20th of January last, I
                            beg leave to transmit to you, with this note, a box which has been sent
                            to me by her Majesty’s government, and which contains one of the cannon
                            balls fired at the Margaret and Jessie by the United States ship Rhode
                            Island, together with the piece of iron struck by it.</p>
                <p>In pursuance of instructions which I have received from her Majesty’s
                            government, I take this opportunity of pressing the United States
                            government for a decision in the case of the Margaret and Jessie and of
                            expressing the regret of her Majesty’s government that the case has not
                            already been satisfactorily disposed of.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
